org.oucs.oxpoints.model
Class OxPoints

java.lang.Object
  org.oucs.oxpoints.model.OxPoints

public class OxPoints
extends java.lang.Object

Forms the gateway to the low level data model.

The OxPoints class represents the data model. It provides methods to interact with the underlying RDF. This can be done either adding RDF directly or using high-level objects such as OxPointsEntity or OxPointsTimeBasedEntity.

It further more provides methods to query the data and to create OxPointsSnapshots (containing a subset of the data).

A description of the underlying data model can be found at RDF and the Time Dimension - Part 2. OxPoints is using the solution with named graphs rather than reification.

OxPoints objects cannot be instantiated directly. The OxPointsFactory has to be used.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Arno Mittelbach
See Also:
OxPointsEntity, OxPointsTimeBasedEntity, OxPointsFactory

remove

public void remove(OxPointsEntity entity,
                   TimeSpan ts)
This method removes an entity from the graph described by the supplied timespan.

Be careful, this method does not make sure that there are no other references to this entity in other graphs. It may well be that other graphs still contain triples that define properties for this entity. If you want to remove all defining triples for this entity use purge(OxPointsEntity)

Parameters:
entity - The entity to be removed
ts - Defines the graph from which the entity should be removed.
See Also:
purge(OxPointsEntity)

containsEntity

public boolean containsEntity(OxPointsEntity entity)
Tests whether the passed entity exists.

It is not tested whether the system has a copy of the entity in that particular form (all the attributes set to specific values). It will just be checked if there is a triple in the system that assigns the entity an RDF type: 

 uri            rdf:type                ?t .

Parameters:
entity - The entity to test.
Returns:
True, if there is some information about this entity stored in the system.
